article.headline: Winston-Salem 68, Norfolk St. 65
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) -- Jamal Durham scored 17 points to lead Winston-Salem State to a 68-65 victory against Norfolk State on Monday night. In a game that featured 17 ties and 20 lead changes, the Rams took the lead for good on Paul Davis' free throw with 2:01 remaining, making it 61-60. Winston-Salem State led by five in the final minute before Kevin Worley hit a 3-pointer with 6 seconds to pull Norfolk State within 67-65. Isiah Tucker made 1-of-2 free throws with 3 seconds left to seal it. Davis had 14 points and 11 rebounds and Roy Peake added 12 points for the Rams (11-15), who have won two straight and three of four. Tony Murphy scored 15 points to lead Norfolk State (14-12), which entered one game behind Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference leader Morgan State but was handed its second straight loss. This one doesn't count in the standings, though, because Winston-Salem State isn't eligible to play in the league tournament until 2009-10. Michael Deloach added 14 points and Brandon Monroe finished with 12 for the Vikings.
